  "prompt": "Why do I see numbers and not contacts' names? In WhatsApp?",
  "response": "If you're seeing numbers instead of contact names in WhatsApp, it usually indicates that the app is not properly syncing with your phone's contacts. Here are a few steps you can take to resolve this issue:\n\n1. **Check Permissions:**\n   - Ensure that WhatsApp has the necessary permissions to access your contacts. You can check this in your phone's settings under 'Apps' or 'Applications,' then select 'WhatsApp,' and check 'Permissions.'\n\n2. **Refresh Contacts:**\n   - Open WhatsApp, go to the 'Chats' tab, and tap on the chat icon to start a new chat. At the top right, tap on the three-dot menu and select 'Refresh.' This will refresh your contact list.\n\n3. **Sync Contacts:**\n   - Go to your phone's settings and check if your accounts (like Google, if you\u2019re using Android) are syncing properly. Ensure that 'Contacts' sync is enabled.\n\n4. **Check Country Code:**\n   - Ensure that the contacts are saved with the correct country code if they are international numbers.\n\n5. **Update WhatsApp:**\n   - Make sure you are using the latest version of WhatsApp. Go to the Google Play Store or Apple App Store and see if there\u2019s an update available.\n\n6. **Restart Your Phone:**\n   - Sometimes, simply restarting your phone can resolve syncing issues.\n\n7. **Reinstall WhatsApp:**\n   - As a last resort, consider uninstalling and then reinstalling WhatsApp. Be sure to back up your chats first to ensure no data is lost.\n\nIf the issue persists after trying these steps, there might be a deeper problem related to the app or your phone\u2019s software, and contacting WhatsApp support or your phone manufacturer might be necessary.",
